description.narrative:
Emission reduction (tCO2eq) as a result of REDD+ AP;
Number of policies, institutions, coordination mechanisms and regulatory frameworks that improve incentives for low-emission planning and development and their effective implementation;
Hectares of land or forests under improved and effective management that contributes to CO2 emission reductions (cumulative of SBP, ATPA and Water Funds).

comment.narrative:
Ecuador has defined a national action plan to reduce emissions from REDD+, but has not made it operational yet;
FREL [2001-2008]: 43.418.126 tCO2eq/y;
PDOTs include some environmental information but do not include actions for GHG emissions reduction. Besides, they are not really operational, and not articulated amongst them; Life Plans include environmental information, but not actions for GHG emissions reduction; one institutionalized mechanism for a national dialogue on climate change: Inter-institutional Committee on Climate Change (CICC);
In total 1,713,879 ha: SBP has 1.48 million ha under conservation, 110,91122 for forest sustainable management, and 70,000 ha under restoration programmes; ATPA-MAGAP contributes to improved and effective management of Agroforestry systems in 7,260 ha; the 3 water funds in 83,201 ha.
